From 24 October until 15 December:

The Oxley Highway will be temporarily closed every Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday between 7am and 4.30pm and every Friday between 7am and 3pm between Knodingbul Road (travelling east) and Forbes River Road (travelling west).

Access to Mount Seaview Road will be maintained for motorists and residents after clearing the Forbes River Road checkpoint.

The Oxley Highway will return to single lane alternating flow traffic arrangements during the NSW summer school holidays with full road closures to resume Tuesday, 30 January 2024.

We expect the full road closures to be in place until about Easter 2024.

Special Event Exemptions – The Oxley Highway will remain open to accommodate the events listed below:

  • Thursday 16 and Friday 17 November (Walcha Motorcycle Rally)
  • Thursday 30 November and Friday 1 December (NSW State Cup Touch Football)
  • Friday 9 February (Walcha Cup Race Meeting)
  • Friday 16 February (Walcha Antique Machinery and Truck Show)
  • Thursday 7 and Friday 8 March (Walcha Show)
properties.diversions: Motorists could consider Waterfall Way or the New England Highway as an alternative route.
